  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\rho_{\\mathrm{vac}}^{T}\n=\n\\frac{1}{u_T^4}\n\\int_{0}^{\\omega_{\\mathrm{cut}}}\n\\eta(\\omega)\\,\n\\hbar\\omega\\,\n\\mathrm{d}\\omega .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nEach vacuum mode of frequency $\\omega$ contributes energy proportional to:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\hbar\\omega .\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe spectral density index $\\eta(\\omega)$ weights the contribution of each frequency:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\eta(\\omega)\\hbar\\omega .\n\\end{equation}\n\nIntegrating over all allowed frequencies up to the cutoff $\\omega_{\\mathrm{cut}}$ gives the weighted vacuum energy:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\int_{0}^{\\omega_{\\mathrm{cut}}}\n\\eta(\\omega)\\hbar\\omega\\,\\mathrm{d}\\omega .\n\\end{equation}\n\nTo convert this to a density in Trawin units, divide by the fourth power of the base unit:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nu_T^4 .\n\\end{equation}\n\nTherefore,\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n\\rho_{\\mathrm{vac}}^{T}\n=\n\\frac{1}{u_T^4}\n\\int_{0}^{\\omega_{\\mathrm{cut}}}\n\\eta(\\omega)\\,\n\\hbar\\omega\\,\n\\mathrm{d}\\omega .\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\n$\\rho_{\\mathrm{vac}}^{T}$ defines vacuum energy density as a spectral integral normalized by the four-dimensional Trawin base scale.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
